SIMPLE: flea-bitten
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flea-bitten
<hw>flea"-bit`ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Bitten by a flea; <as>as, a <ex>flea-bitten</ex>
face</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>White, flecked with minute dots of bay or sorrel; --
said of the color of a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>same as <er>creaky</er>, 1.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> creaky, decrepit, run-down, rundown,
woebegone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fleagh</ent>⟦br⟧
